## Phase 41: Ecosystem Reality & Privacy (Live)
I have successfully implemented the ecosystem and privacy scaling requirements to make the platform feel alive on day one:

- **Algorithmic Views**: Implemented [calculateAlgorithmicViews()](file:///C:/GOLive/lib/utils.ts#41-79) in [utils.ts](file:///C:/GOLive/lib/utils.ts) to deterministically generate realistic, organic-looking views (100-5000+) based on the video ID and time alive. These views now populate the [VideoCard](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoCard.tsx#28-101) components and the Studio dashboard.
- **Privacy Controls**: Added a "Visibility" selector (Public / Private) to the Upload page. Private videos are saved with a hidden category and are seamlessly filtered out of the [Home](file:///C:/GOLive/app/page.tsx#43-47) and [Trending](file:///C:/GOLive/app/trending/page.tsx#24-192) feeds without breaking the database schema.
- **Ecosystem Data Sweep**: Removed all "(Mock)" labels from the Studio and generated deterministic engagement metrics (likes/comments) relative to the algorithmic views.
- **Ecosystem Guide**: Expanded the user seeding script to generate 100 diverse accounts and created [ECOSYSTEM_GUIDE.md](file:///C:/GOLive/ECOSYSTEM_GUIDE.md) detailing how to use them to populate the platform.

A successful production build was executed locally to guarantee these changes will compile flawlessly on Vercel.
